<HEADLINE> Nepali King Accepts PM's Resignation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Nepali King Birendra has
accepted the resignation of Prime Minister Lokendra Bahadur Chand
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Chand resigned followed the passage in the Lower House of a
no-confidence motion against his seven-month-old coalition
government tabled by the main opposition Nepali Congress.
</P>
<P>
Chand will look after the care-taker government till a
successor is named by the King, said a notice issued by the
principal press secretariat of the King.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
