<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Industry up 12.8 Percent in First Nine Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Industrial establishments in
Vietnam achieved a year-to-year increase of 12.8 percent in the
first nine months, Official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The statistics said the industrial output value in this
period was estimated at over 96,000 billion dong (more than 8
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Foreign-invested sector is the largest gainer, grossing 27,596
billion dong (2.29 billion dollars) or an increase of 20.4 percent
against the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
State-run enterprises accounted for 46,178 billion dong
(3.8 billion dollars) or up by 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Non-state sector made up 22,564 billion dong (1.8 billion
billion dollars) or an increase of 20.4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
