<HEADLINE> Mongolian Parliament Members Urge Government to Resign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Members of Parliament from
the Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party (MPRP) today submitted
a draft proposal to the Great Hural (parliament) urging the
current government to resign.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-three of the country's 76 parliament members, mainly from
the MPRP, signed their names to the proposal, which was submitted
by the MPRP Chairman Nambaryn Enhbayar to the Chairman of the
Great Hural Radnasumberlyn Gonchigdorzh, said a report of the
Montsame News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Under Mongolia's law, the Great Hural is required to hold a
special meeting to discuss the resignation of the government if it
is requested to do so by more than one fourth of the
parliament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
