<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Youth Seek Ways to Fight Unemployment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Young people in Tanzania
have demanded the government and parliament to help them tackle
unemployment and other social problems.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment has become a major factor hindering the
advancement of the youth in Tanzania, participants in a seminar
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment has resulted in such vices as child sex,
defilement and drug abuse, the participants said at the seminar,
held for youth development.
</P>
<P>
To solve unemployment and other problems, delegates called on
the government to involve youth in decision making, and proposed
that young people should have their own members in the
parliament.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2025, delegates said, Tanzania primary school
enrollment rate should have risen to 100 percent from present 70
percent, while the life expectancy should have risen from 52 to
70 years. 
