for losses and damage sustained by the Kuwaiti hostile acts."
</P>
<P>
Iraq and Kuwait cut off relationship since Baghdad invaded the
small rich Gulf country in 1990. Both sides have been trading
accusations that one has crossed the other's borders.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League is trying to help lift the seven-year-old U.N.
economic sanctions on Iraq imposed after the Iraqi invasion of
Kuwait in 1990. 
