environmental protection is lagging behind what it should be in
many aspects, which urges China to further strengthen legislation
and supervision in this regard."
</P>
<P>
Li made these remarks today when meeting with foreign and
Chinese participants in the first meeting of the Second Phase of
the China Council for International Co-operation on Environment
and Development (CCICED).
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that the recent 15th National Congress of the
Chinese Communist Party has listed a sustainable development and a
revitalization of China through science and education as a key to
development, which China should stick to in the years to come.
</P>
<P>
The current government and the next will pay due attention
to the issue of environment and development, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that anything that can destroy resources, and
damage the environment for the subsistence of our descendants
should be stopped, and the control-after-pollution lesson should
be drawn on.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that the shift of the economic system from the
traditional planned economy to a socialist market economy, and the
shift of the economic growth mode from extensive to intensive, as
well as the improvement of the quality of China's economic growth
are closely related to environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
China pays equal attention to the developing and saving of
resources, and over the recent years, considerable progress has
been made as regard to energy saving, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China attaches great importance to the
legislation concerning environmental protection, and corresponding
laws and regulations directed against the water, gas, noise, solid
water pollution have been formulated.
</P>
<P>
In the countryside, those seriously polluting township
enterprises have undergone renovation, while in the cities,
progress has been made in different aspects such as the increase
of the gasification proportion, central heating, non-lead gasoline
usage, classified garbage disposal, foul water disposal and etc.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, measures have been taken to prevent the
desertification in the remote areas, Li said, adding China has
stressed the increase of forest coverage, and at present, China
has set up some 800 nature reserves.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the CCICED, since its founding five years ago, has
done an effective job, and its foreign members have put forward
many constructive suggestions which are helpful to China's
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed the hope that the foreign experts, with their
knowledge, speciality and experience, will continue to offer
consultations. The Premier also hoped that Chinese and foreign
members of the council will co-operate closely to score a greater
achievement.  
</P>
</TEXT>
