<HEADLINE> Japanese Loan for Reservoir Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a major water
conservation project funded with soft loans from Japan commenced
today in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
The Baishi Reservoir will be built with 2.07 billion yuan,
including an eight-billion-Japanese-yen loan provided by the
Overseas Economic Cooperation Fund of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The reservoir, scheduled for completion in the year 2,000, will
have a water storage capacity of 1.64 billion cu.m., and will help
control heavy flooding possible in the region once every fifty
years. The reservoir will also provide the region with an
additional 460 million cu.m. of water annually for industrial and
agricultural purposes.
</P>
<P>
Vice-premier Zou Jiahua and a number of Japanese officials
attended today's ground-breaking ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
