<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Increase Environmental Protection Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 5 (Xinhua) -- China will continue to improve
environmental protection, and will cooperate with other counties
to promote sustained sound development.
</P>
<P>
State Councilor Song Jian made the remarks today during an
address to the closing session of the first meeting of the Second
Phase of the China Council for International Cooperation on
Environment and Development.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has intensified ecological protection
and pollution control while expanding its economy. The government
has seriously implemented international environment conventions,
and has extended great efforts to reduce the rate of greenhouse gas
emissions. Related efforts have established environmental
protection with Chinese characteristics, said Song, who also
serves as chairman of the State Council's Environmental Protection
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Song thanked the China Council for International Cooperation on
Environment and Development for its major contributions to
furthering China's environmental protection, and expressed the hope
that the council will provide more advice and creative suggestions.
</P>
<P>
Arthur Holcombe, resident Beijing representative of the United
Nations Development Program (UNDP), noted that the UNDP is
satisfied with the work of the China Council, and will continue to
support the nation's environmental protection projects. He said
the UNDP is also interested in cooperating with China in areas
such as pollution control, protecting biodiversity and promoting
sustained agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
China has recored gratifying achievements in environmental
protection at a time when the nation's economy is in transition
from conventional to sustainable development. China's industrial
enterprises are replacing conventional backward technology with
cleaner production technology. In addition, China has also
recorded new progress in environmental legislation and has greatly
enhanced the general public's awareness of the need for
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Qu Geping, vice-chairman of the first meeting and chairman of
the National People's Congress Environment and Resources
Protection Committee, cited the achievements as a proof of the
fact that China's environmental protection efforts have entered a
new period of development.
</P>
<P>
The China Council for International Cooperation on Environment
and Development, established in 1992, consists of senior officials
and scholars from both at home and abroad, as well as officials
from relevant UN organizations in Beijing. The council advises the
Chinese government on environmental protection and development
issues.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the three-day meeting will discuss issues
ranging from China's environmental economics to energy strategies
for protecting biodiversity. The meeting is expected to provide
valuable recommendations to the Chinese government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
