number of people allegedly missing after being arrested by the
troops or police in Jaffna Peninsula was reduced from 2,568 to
730, due to the finding that some of the names were duplicated.
</P>
<P>
Since June 1996, various international committees and
non-governmental organizations have reported to the Sri Lankan
government that many people disappeared after they were arrested
by the military or police. (Sri Lanka-Missing People)
