<HEADLINE> Construction of China's Longest Expressway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Today marked the beginning of
construction of China's longest expressway.
</P>
<P>
The east-west six-lane expressway will stretch 361 kilometers
from Shenyang in northeast China's Liaoning Province to
Shanhaiguan in northern Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The expressway will be constructed at an estimated cost of 11
billion yuan, including a 200 million US dollars loan from the
Asian Development Bank. The project is scheduled for completion by
the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua attended today's ribbon-cutting
ceremony. 
</P>
