<HEADLINE> Choi Keeps WBA Junior Lightweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 5, (Xinhua) -- Choi Yong-soo of South Korea won
the last three rounds to gain a draw with Japanese challenger
Takanori Hatakeyama here on Sunday, retaining his World Boxing
Association junior lightweight title.
</P>
<P>
It was Choi's sixth successful defense of the title that he won
from Argentine Victor Hugo Paz in Salta, Argentina, on October 21,
1995.
</P>
<P>
There were no knockdowns during the 12-round bout. Judge Marcos
Torres of Panama scored the fight 116-114 for Hatakeyama. Derek
Milham of Australia had it 116-114 for Choi. And Art Luries of the
United States had it 114-114.
</P>
<P>
It was the South Korean's first draw after 23 victories,
including 13 knockouts, and two defeats.
</P>
<P>
It also was the first draw for the 11th-ranked Japanese
challenger, who entered the fight with 20 victories, including 16
knockdown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
