<HEADLINE> 76 Local Investors Operate in Ethiopian City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Seventy-six local investors
have begun operation in Dire Dawa, the second largest
city in Ethiopia after receiving investment licenses, said a report
reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, five foreign investors have applied for the
undertaking of project study, the report added.
</P>
<P>
The Dire Dawa administration investment office was quoted by
the report as saying that the local entrepreneurs have a combined
capital of over 232 million Birr (about 34 million US Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The office said due to the conducive investment atmosphere
existing in the administration, which is located at the middle of
850 kms of Addis Ababa-Djibouti Railway, most of the local
entrepreneurs are engaged in agro-industry development activities
and health, education and commercial activities.
</P>
<P>
As the topography of the administration is suitable for trade,
investors can easily supply their products to domestic and
foreign markets, the office added. 
</P>
