<HEADLINE> International Population Conference to Be Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The 23rd IUSSP General
Population Conference is scheduled to be held in Beijing from
October 12 through 17.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that China has hosted the four-yearly
conference of the International Union of Scientific Study of
Population (IUSSP).
</P>
<P>
More than 1,300 specialists and scholars from 80-plus countries
and regions, as well as representatives from some international
organizations will attend the conference, jointly organized by
China Population Association, the State Family Planning
Commission, the United Nations Population Fund, and the IUSSP.
</P>
<P>
The conference will include two plenary sessions, a symposium
on demography of China, 23 panel discussions, and 42 informal
panel discussions, according to the China Organizing Committee of
the conference.
</P>
<P>
The IUSSP, established in 1928, is an important international
academic organization in population study whose most important
activity is the four-yearly conference. The Union has been devoted
to prompting governments, international organizations and the
general public to show more concern for the population issue.
</P>
</TEXT>
