<HEADLINE> East China Province Improving Mobile and Multi-Media Communications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 5 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian province is
increasing the handling capacity of the local mobile
telecommunications network to one million lines and will couple
its public multi-media system to a national network this year.
</P>
<P>
The province is spending six billion yuan on expanding the
local mobile telecommunications network, which now has had a
handling capacity of 900,000 lines.
</P>
<P>
It has also finished a larg part of technological improvements
on the local public multi-media network, and work on five
information centers in Sanming, Nanping, Ningde, Putian and
Longyan is well under way.
</P>
<P>
Over the next three years, the province plans to spend 20
billion yuan on the two sectors to increase the handling capacity
of its mobile telecommunications network to three million lines
and to build a broad-band asynchronous transport mode (ATM)
multi-media network. 
</P>
