<HEADLINE> Southwest Nigerian State Worried by Lunatics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Residents of many towns in Osun
state, southwest Nigeria, can no longer walk freely at night
following the invasion of major streets by lunatics.
</P>
<P>
According to "New Nigeria" today, some of the lunatics,
especially the males, often terrorize residents in where they
stay, including the capital city.
</P>
<P>
The official newspaper which noted the fears created by the
"ugly development" did not say where and why the lunatics came
from.
</P>
<P>
It said the lunatics had taken over most of the uncompleted
buildings in the state while some moved into commercial shops
thus scaring customers away.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a government official as saying the State
Ministry of Youths and Social Development was making every best
possible effort to arrest the situation.
</P>
<P>
However, the press officer said the ministry was handicapped
for the fact that it was not in the best position to identify who
"is a lunatic or not" as such could only be done by the health
authorities.
</P>
<P>
But the government would soon put in place necessary
modalities at ridding the state of lunatics, said sources at the
State Ministry of Health. 
</P>
</TEXT>
