<HEADLINE> Over 460 Mozambicans Repatriated From Swaziland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 5 (Xinhua) -- More than 460 Mozambicans have
been repatriated from Swaziland since September 22, said Roque
Muquessuane, head of Mozambique's Namaacha County, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This means that more than 40 Mozambicans are forced to be
repatriated every day, according to local paper "Domingo" today.
</P>
<P>
The magistrate of the border county said that there are more
Mozambicans in Swaziland's prisons waiting to be repatriated,
adding that the move of the neighboring country has caused some
problems threatening social safety in his county town.
</P>
<P>
He said that along the Mozambique-Swaziland border, there
often occurs incidents of illegally crossing the border,
smuggling and cattle rustling, but in the past the two countries
had managed to solve the problems properly for the sake of good
neighborliness.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican official said that they did not know why the
Swazi authorities repatriated Mozambicans, adding the move by the
Swazi side was out of expectation. 
</P>
