<HEADLINE> Syria Keeps Door Open to Peace Process: Syrian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Defense Minister General
Mustafa Tlass has announced that Syria still adheres to the peace
process and keeps the door open despite the intransigent policy of
Israeli government.
</P>
<P>
Tlass' statement came in a TV interview with the Syrian
Satellite Channel today on the 24th anniversary of the
Arab-Israeli 1973 war.
</P>
<P>
General Tlass, who is also Deputy Commander in Chief of the
Syrian Armed Forces, denounced the policy adopted by the
Netanyahu government for its rejection to peace and the
U.N. resolution and for its failure to commit itself to the
pledges made by former Israeli governments.
</P>
<P>
"Syria accepted the U.S. initiative which called for convening
a peace conference in Madrid on the basis of the relevant
U.N. resolutions and the land-for-peace principle, and still
adheres to the peace process," Tlass said.
</P>
<P>
"We are peace-seekers. The international community is
absolutely aware of our consistent attitude, and the whole world
is aware that it is Israel which is attempting to blast the peace
process and is subsequently responsible for the failure and has
to take the consequences," he added.
</P>
<P>
Syria insists that the Syrian-Israeli peace negotiations should
resume from where they halted in May, 1996, but Netanyahu
government insists that these negotiations should start anew
without any preconditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
