<HEADLINE> Iraq Exports 1.6 Million Barrels of Oil Per Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Iraq has managed to export 1.6
million barrels of oil per day, running against time under the
oil-for-food deal, an Iraqi oil official announced.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi newspaper "Al-Jomhouriya" today quoted Saddam Zein
El-Hassan, Executive Director of Iraq's Oil-Marketing Authority,
as saying that Iraq has managed in the past 22 days to export oil
valuing more than 50 percent as much as the value set for its oil
exports in the first 90 days of the second phase of the
oil-for-food deal.
</P>
<P>
El-Hassan added that the first three months period of the
second phase of the oil-for-food deal would expire today, and in
accordance with the amendment introduced to the U.N. Resolution
1111, the second period would start tomorrow and would last up to
December.
</P>
<P>
"It is a record time if it is taken into consideration that
several steps have to be taken after a contract for selling oil
is signed," the Iraqi oil official remarked.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. agreed last June to extend its oil-for-food deal with
Iraq, but the later started exporting its oil only in mid-August
in protest against delaying the arrival of food and medical
supplies in Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
