for the rural areas of Angola. After graduation from the school,
the graduates must teach in primary or middle schools in the
countryside to reduce illiteracy and promote development there.
</P>
<P>
The "People Aid People" is expected to set up 16 teachers
training schools in Angola to boost the development of education
in Angola. So far, three such schools including the "Future
Teachers" in Huambo has been established. 
