<HEADLINE> Northeast China City Developing Bonded Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to a series of
preferential polices, the Dalian Bonded Zone in this coastal city
in northeast China has become a popular investment spot for
international trade, industrial processing, storage, and other
businesses.
</P>
<P>
The bonded zone was set up in 1992 and is the only zone of its
kind in northeast China. It has 1,480 overseas- and
domestic-funded projects, 696 of which have attracted one billion
US dollars of contractual investment from various countries.
</P>
<P>
Encouraged by the zone's investment policies and management
methods, which are similar to those used abroad, a large number of
businesses have gotten involved in international trade.
</P>
<P>
The bonded zone has been built as Dalian's largest storage
base, and has been provided with exhibition halls and
petrochemical and automobile trading areas. The zone did three
billion yuan worth of business in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
A number of the city's state enterprises and trade companies
are being encouraged to do business in the zone, as part of a
strategy to help them develop the export-oriented economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
