<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Trade Minister on Sino-US Economic Ties (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dealing with bilateral economic and trade problems on basis
of mutual respect, equality, and mutual understanding is a basic
principle of state-to-state economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
In reviewing the development of Sino-US relations, one can see
that they can grow smoothly when both sides handle problems in an
objective, reasonable and positive way, and if not, difficulties
can occur.
</P>
<P>
Experience tells us that no problem can be solved and there may
be adverse effects when economic and trade problems are used as
bargaining tools for domestic politics or if one side adopts an
unreasonable attitude and threatens the other with retaliation.
</P>
<P>
Sino-US economic and trade ties can only mature and develop in
a healthy way when the two sides eliminate non-trade factors and
resolve problems and expand cooperation, and that is in the
interest of the two peoples. Both governments need to adopt
necessary measures to encourage positive factors and overcome
negative ones and become firm backings to the development of
bilateral trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has made great efforts in developing
Sino-US trade and economic cooperation and has sent delegations
to the U.S. many times to try to improve the trade balance and we
hope that the U.S. will take action as soon as possible to restore
or enforce trade promotion programs to create a more favorable
environment for bilateral trade economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
It should be noted that there are many favorable conditions for
Sino-US trade and economic cooperation development. The
complimentary nature of the two economies, for one thing, is a
good basis for cooperation and people in industry and business
communities of both countries are enthusiastic about cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Both governments fully recognize the importance of Sino-US
economic and trade ties and the existing cooperation offers many
examples of success for future growth. The strong growth of the
Asia-Pacific economies provide a good chance for cooperation
between China and the United States, both of which are on the
Pacific rim.
</P>
<P>
The recent 15th Congress of the Chinese Communist Party
provided a blueprint for future development in China, which will
open even wider to the rest of the world, creating new
opportunities for expanded economic cooperation and trade with
all other countries.
</P>
<P>
As long as both China and the United States cherish the hard-won
progress and act positively and in a spirit of trust, eliminate
prejudice, reduce differences, and create the future together,
they will push Sino-US economic and trade relations to a new level.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971005.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-05 </DATE_TIME>
