<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Developing Domestic Waste Utilization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Scientists in China's leading
industrial city have developed a device of automatically sorting
domestic waste and recycling certain items.
</P>
<P>
The device was developed by scientists of the Shanghai
Invention Association to sort inorganic waste like sand, stone,
brick, metal, and plastic materials for recycling.
</P>
<P>
The whole process takes place in sealed conditions so that it
does not produce pollution a second time.
</P>
<P>
Scientists say that the device has a daily waste disposal
capacity of 100 tons, from which combustible gas can be produced
for 500 households for daily use, along with 50 tons of quality
fertilizer, building materials and recycled rubber.
</P>
<P>
They said the device occupies only one hectare of land and can
be put either aboveground or underground. Its annual recycled
resources value could be from 2 million to 4 million yuan (250,000
to 500,000 million dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
