<HEADLINE> Biaggi Wins Fourth World 250cc Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Italian Max Biaggi retained his
fourth world 250cc motorcycle championship with a second place in
the Australian Grand Prix in Phillip Island on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Biaggi had to finish runner-up in the final season race while
Waldmann took the victory with 5.890 seconds ahead of Biaggi, and
French Elf Tech Honda rider Olivier Jacque third, a further 27.251
seconds away.
</P>
<P>
It was Biaggi's 54th podium finish and he finished the season
with 250 points from Waldmann 248 and Harada third on 235 points.
</P>
<P>
Biaggi won five of the 15 races at Malaysia, Italy, Imola,
Czech Republic and Indonesia, while Waldmann shared four
successes: Spain, Britain, Catalunya (Spain) and Australia.
</P>
