<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Minister on Sino-U.S. Economic Ties (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China is the largest developing country and the U.S. is the
largest developed country. Their difference in reserves of natural
resources, industrial structures, and levels of consumption
decides that the two countries can supplement each other
economically through trade, therefore two-way trade and economic
cooperation have certain natural advantages and bright prospects.
</P>
<P>
China's cheap and quality products are attractive to Americans
and American goods are well received in China. China's enormous
markets and abundent labor resources are major factors which make
many American companies to give top priority to China when
expanding their businesses overseas. At the same time, many Chinese
companies regard U.S. companies as ideal partners, with their
advanced science and technology, sufficient funding, and
efficient management skills.
</P>
<P>
China is one of the major suppliers of textile products, garments,
shoes, household appliances, toys, and luggage bags and cases for
the U.S. and an important market for America's aircrafts, power
equipment, machinery, electronics, instruments, telecommunications
equipment, chemical fertilizers, and agricultural products like
grain and cotton.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, one out of every 10 of Boeing's aircrafts
has been sold to China. By the end of last year, Boeing had sold
a total of 222 passenger planes to China.
</P>
<P>
China has also become the sixth largest export destination for
America's agricultural products, and more than 200 of the 500 top
companies in the U.S. have trade links and economic cooperation
with China.
</P>
<P>
The steady development of the Sino-U.S. economic ties and trade
is conducive to the economic prosperity of both countries and
two-way trade has created more than 300,000 highly-paid jobs and,
indirectly, almost a million jobs for the United States alone.
</P>
<P>
Two-way investment and bilateral economic cooperation have
helped the economic vitality and prosperity of the two
countries. Today with peace and development as the major attention
of the world, Sino-U.S. trade and economic cooperation becomes an
important factor for stabilizing bilateral relations and a source
for further advancement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971005.0124 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-05 </DATE_TIME>
