<HEADLINE> Ueda Wins Australian Motorcycling GP 125cc Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Noboru Ueda won the
Australian Motorcycle Grand Prix 125cc race in Phillip Island,
Australia, Sunday on a Honda.
</P>
<P>
Ueda pulled away over the final four laps of the 23-lap race to
beat Aprilia's Japanese rider, Kazuto Sakata, by 1.536 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Another Japanese, Tomomi Manako on a Honda, edged out Italian
Roberto Locatelli for third place, 1.632 seconds away.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Valentino Rossi, who had already locked up the 125cc
world title, suffered engine problems mid-race with his Aprilia
and finished sixth, his lowest place of the season.
</P>
<P>
Ueda finished second in the championship to 18-year-old Rossi,
who is moving up to the 250cc class next season.
</P>
<P>
Another Japanese rider Youichi Ui, on a Yamaha, tumbled out on
cold tyres inside the first lap while leading the field. He was
uninjured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
