<HEADLINE> Opposition FORD-People Registered in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 5 (Xinhua) --The Kenneth Matiba faction of
opposition FORD-Asili has been registered as an independent
political party, the Sunday Nation reported today.
</P>
<P>
The new party is named the Forum for the Restoration of
Democracy for the People (FORD-People) registered last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The registration brought an end to a
protracted battle for supremacy and control of Opposition
FORD-Asili between Matiba and the Martin Shikuku group, said
the report.
</P>
<P>
The development is reminiscent of the 1992 split in the
original FORD movement, following protracted disagreements
between Matiba and Jaramogi Oginga Odinga.
</P>
<P>
The new party has Matiba as chairman, Stephen Musila as
vice-chairman, Kimani wa Nyoike as secretary-general and John
Chebii as treasurer.
</P>
<P>
FORD-P's registration brings to 12 the number of political
parties in the East African country.
</P>
<P>
The registration came on the last day of the deadline
set by the Inter-Parties Parliamentary Group reforms
package which gives 14 days from the day of adoption by the
registrar to process all pending political party applications.
</P>
<P>
Registrar-General Omondi Mbago is expected to go public on
Monday on the political parties he has agreed to register and
give reasons why others cannot be registered.
</P>
<P>
Ungistered Safina, the Islamic Party of Kenya, and others are
awaiting Mbago's decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
