ROME -- An explosion occurred Saturday in a firework factory in
Salerno, southern Italy, killing the owner and his eldest son,
police said.
</P>
<P>
Firemen took four hours to put out a fire triggered off by the
explosion. The explosion was caused by short circuit, according to
the police. (Italy-Explosion)
</P>
