</P>
<P>
These include three billion US dollars in imports and nearly
2.8 billion US dollars in exports, a rise of 17.8 percent and 22.2
percent over the same period in 1996, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 45 percent of the foreign trade, or 2.6 billion US
dollars, came from overseas-funded enterprises, and the
remaining 55 percent, from state businesses.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of overseas-funded enterprises in the area
are the result of a push for increased foreign trade. The speedy
development of the processing trade has also helped boost foreign
trade.
</P>
<P>
During the eight-month period foreign trade involving the
processing of imported raw materials by overseas-funded companies
was nearly 1.1 billion US dollars, a 64 percent increase over the
same period of 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
