<HEADLINE> Sub-Saharan Counntnries Urged to Promote Mining </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Sub-Saharan countries in
Africa have been urged to promote small scale mining to complement
agriculture which still enjoys more support.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by mining experts and geologists who concluded
their three-day international conference on small scale mining in Dar
es Salaam earlier this week, the Sunday News reported today.
</P>
<P>
They said small scale mining has big potential for the economies of
many countries if well developed.
</P>
<P>
They cited Tanzania where a bigger portion of the proceeds from the
mineral sector is generated through mining activities, while small
scale miners are scattered across the country.
</P>
<P>
"Our governments should ensure economic sustainability of small
scale mining by providing extension services and markets for the
minerals," the experts said in their resolutions.
</P>
<P>
They called on financial institutions, including the banks, "to
take more interest in mining business including floating shares in the
stock exchange".
</P>
<P>
They also noted that the environmental aspects of small scale
mining should be fully addressed through enforcement of relevant laws
and policies as well as sensitization of miners on environmentally
friendly mining techniques. 
