COLOMBO, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The ruling Sri Lanka Freedom
Party's (SLFP) plan to resume political activities in war-torn
Jaffna suffered a body blow on Friday night when the party's chief
organizer was shot dead in Jaffna, military sources disclosed here
today.
</P>
<P>
They said the SLFP's chief organizer S. Dharmalingam, a Tamil,
was shot dead at point blank range at his residence three
kilometers off Jaffna town at about 8:40 Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Investigators said they didn't know the motive of the killing
of 57-year-old Dharmalingam. They suspected the action could be
taken by the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) gunman.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a bloody ethnic war for a
separate state of their own for 14 years in Sri Lanka. The war so
far has claimed more than 55,000 lives.  
</P>
</TEXT>
