<HEADLINE> Mafia Fugitive Arrested in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Italian and Spanish authorities
arrested a top-level Mafia figure, Giovannello Greco, on the
Spanish island of Ibiza today, police said.
</P>
<P>
Greco, sentenced to 15 years in prison for Mafia association
and murder during the Mafia maxi-trial in the early 1980s, had
been on the run for 16 years before he was tracked down today by
police investigators of Sicilian capital Palermo.
</P>
<P>
Greco and others were said to be preparing their return to
Sicily to exact reverge on their sworn enemies and to organize the
forces who had lost the 1980s Mafia wars.
</P>
<P>
"The arrest of a top-level Mafia figure like Giovannello Greco
is an important investigative success," Palermo police chief
Antonino Manganelli said, adding that police were searching the
apartment in which Greco was found.
</P>
<P>
"In the next few hours, we should know what his role was (in
the Mafia) and the veracity of the `legend' that he was wanted in
Palermo to organize the losing forces," he said.
</P>
<P>
The chairman of the Parliamentary anti-Mafia commission,
Ottaviano Del Turco, called the arrest "another big step in the
fight against what is left of the old guard of Palermo's Cosa
Nostra." 
</P>
</TEXT>
