has profound bearing over the country's reform, opening-up and
socialist modernization and construction.
</P>
<P>
-- Hainan Province, the largest special economic zone of China,
has attracted more than six billion US dollars of foreign
investment, and over 30 billion yuan of domestic investment during
the past nine years.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese workers have dug a canal from the Yangtze River to
divert ships from the construction site of the Three Gorges Dam
where work will be be started early next month.
</P>
<P>
Starting October 6, normal navigation will be stopped on the
main stream of the Yangtze in the dam area and all the ships will
direct their courses along the canal named "Daoliu Ming Canal."
</P>
<P>
The country's navigation department today began to supervise
operation on the canal, which is 3,726 meters long, 350 meters
wide and 58 meters deep. The canal is said to be deeper and wider
than the Suez and Panama canals.
</P>
<P>
Business Weekly of China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- China's move to slash tariffs on car imports starting
October 1 has encountered mixed responses, triggering another
round of debate over what is the way out for the frail auto
industry. The tariff on sedans has been reduced from 120 percent
to 100 percent while the import tax levied on common cars has been
cut from 100 percent to 80 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Mineral resources discovered in China over the past five
years will bring golden opportunities for the economic take-off of
the country's central and western regions.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,100 locations of solid mineral deposits were
discovered during the period while about 500 old mineral deposit
sites added new reserves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
