<HEADLINE> Belarus Opposed to NATO Expanding Military Institutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Belarussian Foreign Minister Ivan
Antonovich said today that his country is opposed to NATO's plans
to expand its military institutions.
</P>
<P>
He made the comment at the United Nations' General Assembly,
the Interfax news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Belarus holds that NATO should become a peace- and
security-keeping organization, Antonovich said.
</P>
<P>
It is of much importance for NATO to revise its military goals,
the top diplomat said.
</P>
<P>
He warned that Minsk will have to reconsider its stand on
national defense if any unfriendly country or military
organization appears on its western border.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin also said last week that his
country hopes the North Atlantic Treaty Organization should turn
into a political or at least a peace-keeping organization rather
than remaining as a military alliance, the Itar-Tass News Agency
reported Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
