<HEADLINE> WBO Super-featherweight Title Still Uncertain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Julien Lorcy of France and
Arnulfo Castillo of Mexico had to settle a second successive draw
Saturday night, leaving the WBO super-featherweight title still
vacant.
</P>
<P>
Lorcy and Castillo fought to a draw for the first time on March
1 when they vied for the vacant title, and the judges were again
uncertain the result after 12 fiercely-contested rounds this
time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
