<HEADLINE> Philippoussis, Rusedski Enter Swiss ATP Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Mark Philippoussis and Greg
Rusedski beat their rivals respectively Saturday to set up a
showdown in the million-dollar Swiss Indoors ATP Tour tennis
tournament in Basel, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Australian Philippoussis beat Britain's Tim Henman 7-6 (7/2),
6-4 while Rusedski of Britain scored a 6-7 (5/7), 6-3, 7-5 win
over seventh-seeded Czech player Petr Korda.
</P>
<P>
US Open semi-finalist Rusedski, who has made at least the
quarter-finals in each of his last six tournaments, hammered down
19 aces in a desperately-tight battle between two left-handers.
</P>
<P>
Philippoussis, meanwhile, reached a final for the second
straight week when he beat Henman.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Australian, who lost to Germany's Nicolas
Kiefer in the Toulouse tournament final in France last week,
triumphed in one hour 27 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The final, with a 138,000 dollar first prize at stake, will
start on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
