<HEADLINE> France Lead in Fed Cup Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Sandrine Testud and Mary Pierce
won the opening two rubbers in the Fed Cup final in Netherlands on
Saturday to give France a 2-0 lead over the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Testud, ranked 14th in the world, beat Brenda
Schultz-McCarthy 6-4, 4-6, 6-3, in 106 minutes, while Pierce
disposed of Miriam Oremans 6-4, 6-1 in 72 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The unpredictable Pierce, ranked eighth in the world and
preferred to veteran Nathalie Tauziat for the singles, struggled
early on in her tie with the 50th ranked Oremans as she trailed
0-40 on her first service game and had to stave off five break
points in the first two service games while failing to win a point
on the Dutchwoman's first two service games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
