<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Emphasizes Family Commitment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 4 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
on Saturday called on the nation to strengthen families.
</P>
<P>
"The need for men to take responsibility for themselves and
their families is something that unites Americans of all faiths
and backgrounds," Clinton said in his weekly radio address in
coincidence with a gathering in downtown Washington.
</P>
<P>
Organized by Promise Keepers, a fast-growing Christian movement
in the United States, the rally featured more than 40 speakers.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said he believed that members of the movement "are
willing to reassume their responsibilities to the families and to
their children and therefore to our future."
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1990 by Bill MaCartney, then a football coach at the
University of Colorado, Promise Keepers has been organizing
all-male weekend meetings for several years.
</P>
<P>
Promise Keepers urges men to be good husbands and fathers.
</P>
</TEXT>
